<Body>If governmental authority rests on divine right, then atheists are people who oppose the legitimacy of that authority, regardless of who is in charge. This makes them a threat, albeit a small one, to any group who thinks their god placed the current leaders in power. (Side-question: does discontentment with political leaders drive significant segments of the population to reject divine right and question notions of omnipresence?)<Body>

